Web dev's time is:
20% remember how to center div;
40% google how to center div;
40% copying center from previuos page;

1. You don't need to know everything -> It's more about understanding pattern than rememberring/learning everything (just like cooking);
2. Learn how to Learn -> Best way is writing code. Switch from consumer mode to creater mode;
3. Perfection is a Trap/Lie -> in a very relative/subjective/fast-changing world no body can write flawless/perfect code. Done is better than perfection, finished ugly code is better than perfect code that takes huge time to be finished and never leaves your laptop;
4. You will never feel ready, start anyway -> You don't need to be confident, you just need to be willing. Start Messy, Start Scary, Just Start;
5. The Real-Skill is Problem-Solving -> Start Focusing Less on 'What to write' and more on 'Why it is written that way';
6. Nobody cares about your Code, They care about what it Does -> Everyone (End-User, Client, Your Boss) wants the result but not what's happening under the hood. So, write codes that solves problems (if it's clean and elegent too - that's light over light) rather than sleeping over writing perfect code. Value is better than Vanity;
7. Burnout is Real so Protect your Energy -> Your Motivation, Desire and Want can turn into Exhaustion, Confusion, and Wandering;

